South African Coal Export Prices Rise for First Week in Seven

-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 
2011-12-05T12:39:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-05/south-african-coal-export-prices-rise-for-first-week-in-seven.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, rose for the first week in seven.  Prices  increased 22 cents, or 0.2 percent, last week to an
average $102.52 a metric ton, following a 3.4 percent decline in
the week ended Nov. 25, according to data on Bloomberg from
researcher IHS McCloskey. The price quoted is on a free-on-board
basis, excluding delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  